1. Project Overview

Purpose

This project is a browser-based tinnitus sound therapy application designed to generate customizable therapeutic audio directly in the user's web browser. It requires no installation, no backend server, and no plugins — all audio is synthesized in real time using the Web Audio API.

The application provides two distinct therapy modes:

- Standard Sound Therapy — colored noise generation (white, pink, brown) with adjustable volume and optional frequency shaping.
- Decorrelated Sound Therapy — independent noise streams delivered to left and right ears, preventing the brain from "locking on" to a single pattern and promoting habituation.

Who This Is For

- Individuals with subjective tinnitus (ringing, buzzing, hissing) seeking non-invasive relief.
- People with tonal tinnitus paired with moderate hearing loss who want to supplement hearing aid therapy.
- Audiologists, therapists, and clinicians looking for an accessible client-side tool.
- Developers interested in Web Audio API applications for therapeutic use.

Design Principles

| Principle | Implementation |
|---|---|
| Privacy-first | All processing runs locally in the browser. No data is collected, stored, or transmitted. |
| Zero dependencies | Pure HTML, CSS, and vanilla JavaScript. No frameworks, no CDN calls, no npm packages. |
| Offline-capable | Once loaded, the application functions without an internet connection. |
| Accessible | Keyboard-navigable controls, ARIA labels, high-contrast color scheme, responsive layout. |
| Evidence-informed | Sound therapy approaches are grounded in published audiological research. |

