6. decorrelated.html — Decorrelated Sound Therapy

Purpose

This page provides an advanced therapy mode that generates two independent noise streams — one for each ear. This prevents the auditory system from consolidating the sound into a single "ignorable" source, promoting deeper and more sustained habituation.

How Decorrelation Works

1. Two separate noise buffers are generated using the same algorithm (e.g., both pink noise), but with different random seeds.
2. Buffer A is routed exclusively to the left channel.
3. Buffer B is routed exclusively to the right channel.
4. The listener perceives a wide, spatially diffuse sound field that is harder for the brain to habituate to (in the negative, adaptation sense).
5. Both streams share the same spectral characteristics, so the therapy remains balanced and comfortable.

