| Uncertain / mixed | Pink noise | Most natural-sounding; good default |

Volume Guidelines

- Target level: Just below the perceived loudness of your tinnitus. You should still be able to hear your tinnitus faintly through the noise — this is the "mixing point" where habituation occurs most effectively.
- Never exceed comfortable levels. Sound therapy should feel soothing, not stressful.
- For sleep: Set volume lower than your daytime preference and use the timer with the fade-out feature.

