8. Technical Architecture

Web Audio API Signal Flow

Standard Mode

`
OscillatorNode / AudioBufferSourceNode (noise)
        │
        ▼
BiquadFilterNode (lowpass — rolloff control)
        │
        ▼
   GainNode (volume)
        │
        ▼
AudioContext.destination (speakers / headphones)
`

Decorrelated Mode

`
AudioBufferSourceNode (left noise)     AudioBufferSourceNode (right noise)
        │                                       │
        ▼                                       ▼
   GainNode (left level)                  GainNode (right level)
        │                                       │
        ▼                                       ▼
ChannelMergerNode ───────────────────────────────┘
        │ (input 0 = left, input 1 = right)
        ▼
   GainNode (master volume)
        │
        ▼
AudioContext.destination (headphones)
`

Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| Pre-generated buffers (4s) with looping | Avoids per-sample ScriptProcessorNode overhead. AudioWorklets are faster but less compatible. 4 seconds provides sufficient randomness to prevent audible looping artifacts. |
| Voss-McCartney for pink noise | O(n) complexity with good spectral accuracy. Alternatives (Paul Kellet's IIR filter) have slightly better accuracy but are more complex to implement and debug. |
| Leaky integrator for brown noise | Simple, stable, and prevents DC offset accumulation that can damage speakers or cause distortion. |
| setTargetAtTime for parameter changes | Exponential smoothing prevents clicks and pops from abrupt value changes. The 50ms time constant is fast enough to feel responsive but slow enough to avoid artifacts. |
| No external audio files | Synthesized noise is infinitely variable, adds zero network latency, works offline, and avoids copyright issues. |
| No frameworks | Minimizes attack surface, load time, and maintenance burden. The application is simple enough that vanilla JS is clearer and faster. |

Security & Privacy Model

- No network requests after initial page load.
- No cookies, localStorage, or sessionStorage used (timer state is in-memory only).
- No analytics, tracking, or telemetry of any kind.
- No microphone or camera access requested.
- Content Security Policy headers recommended for deployment:

`
Content-Security-Policy:
    default-src 'self';
    script-src 'self';
    style-src 'self';
    img-src 'self';
    media-src 'none';
    connect-src 'none';
    frame-src 'none';
`

